post_text: HEY SPARTANS FANS!!! The Spartans will be back under the lights tomorrow night (9/11) at West Monona! This is our chance to thank you for protecting this community and this great Nation! GO SPARTANS!!!

post_text: On Thursday, August 20th, the elementary will be having a non-traditional back to school night! We would love to see our students for a quick supply drop off. This will be an opportunity for families to drive up, drop off, and say “hello!” We want all parents and students to have a chance to drop off their backpacks before the first day and give the parents a chance to meet their child’s teacher. It will be similar to the way we did supply pick up in the spring. Each grade level will be assigned a specific door and time frame to arrive at the school. Parents and students will stop at their grade level door where the grade level teachers will greet you in the vehicle. Then the teachers will take your backpack and supplies in the building to put them in your child’s cubby, locker, or on their hook. Their supplies will be waiting for them when they arrive on Monday! Here are the drop off times and door assignments:

post_text:
Outside groups are not allowed by law to bring food in the school to sell or donate during the COVID Pandemic. Therefore, we will not be having any tailgates at football games this year.

Iowa Law--
Concession stands at a sporting, social, community, leisure, or recreational gathering or event, including but not limited to a parade, festival, convention, or fundraiser, must follow the Guidance for Iowa Concession Stands, Temporary Food Events, and Farmers Markets During COVID-19.

Concession stands that are located on school property are not allowed to operate at this time. This
includes concessions operated by an entity which independently holds a food establishment license
separate from the school’s food license (e.g., a school booster organization or other independent
contractor). This also includes concession stands licensed as Temporary Food Establishments and
Mobile Food Units providing concessions.

tim.chesnut@westmonona.org

post_text:
Teachers on Parade!

What: Teachers on Parade
Who: West Monona students that want to see and wave at their teachers!
When: Wednesday, April 1, 2020, 5:30 p.m.
Where: The parade will be going up and down the numbered streets of Onawa (see attached parade route)

More information:

*To follow social distancing rules, we will not throw candy. If you wish to make signs to tell the teachers hello, that would be great!
*Students that live in the country, in a different town, or not on a numbered street are encouraged to sit along the parade route while practicing social distancing.
*The plan is to go up and down the numbered streets in Onawa. Students can just step out their front door and wave to us from there.
*The police will escort us through town. Behind the police car will be John Adams in a bus and we will follow the bus.

post_text:
West Monona Speech students had a good day at the District Individual Speech Contest at Woodbury Central on Saturday, February 29th.

Lexi Lander and Garrett Heisterkamp were awarded Division 1 ratings in the category of Public Address. Reed Reicks scored a "1" in the very difficult category of Solo Improvisation.

Other students awarded Division 2 ratings included:

Lillie Schild for Acting
Nedelle Smartt for Storytelling
Olivia Phipps for Interpretive Reading - Poetry
Alexys McLeod for Interpretive Reading - Prose
Rosara Reicks for Solo Improvisation
Reed Reicks for Public Address

State Individual Contest will be held on March 14, 2020 at Kuemper Catholic High School.
